'''Basic For Qt''' (formerly KBasic) is the name of an [[object-oriented]] version of the [[BASIC programming language]], as well as an [[integrated development environment]]. It is designed to run on multiple platforms. Pre-compiled binaries are available for Mac, Windows and a few Linux distributions including [[Ubuntu operating system|Ubuntu]]. Source code is also available.

The project is [[abandonware]] at this point.{{Citation needed|date=January 2017}}

