{{BLP refimprove|date=August 2018}} {{Spanish name|Fernández-Savater|Martín}} {{Infobox philosopher | name = Fernando Savater | image = Fernando Savater by Gonzalo Merat.jpg | caption = Portrait of Spanish philosopher Fernando Savater for the magazine ''Jot Down'' | birth_name = Fernando Fernández-Savater Martín | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1947|06|21|df=y}} | birth_place = [[San Sebastián]], [[Basque Country (autonomous community)|Basque Country]], [[Spain]] | alma_mater = [[Universidad Complutense de Madrid]] | influences = {{hlist|[[Nietzsche]]|[[Cioran]]|[[Spinoza]]}} | website = {{URL|www.fernandosavater.com}} }}
'''Fernando Fernández-Savater Martín''' (born 21 June 1947 at Basque city of San Sebastián) is one of [[Spain]]'s most popular living [[philosophers]], as well as an [[essayist]] and celebrated author.
Born in [[San Sebastián]], he was an [[Ethics]] professor at the [[University of the Basque Country]] for over a decade. Presently he is a [[Philosophy]] professor at the [[Complutense University of Madrid]]. He has won several accolades for his literary work, which covers issues as diverse as contemporary ethics, politics, cinema and literary studies. In 1990, Savater and columnist and publisher, [[Javier Pradera]], founded the magazine, ''Claves de Razón Práctica''.<ref>{{cite news |first=José Andrés |last=Rojo |title=The watchman of Spain's transition signs off |url=https://elpais.com/elpais/2011/11/21/inenglish/1321856446_850210.html |newspaper=[[El País]] |date=21 November 2011 |access-date=23 November 2011 |language=es |location=Madrid}}</ref>
He has taken an active part in several organizations engaged with peace in the Basque Country and against [[ETA (separatist group)|terrorism]] and [[Basque nationalism]], such as ''Movimiento por la Paz y la No Violencia'', ''Gesto por la Paz'', ''[[Foro Ermua]]'', and currently ''[[¡Basta Ya!]]''
He defines himself as an [[atheistic]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://bloc.mabosch.info/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/4.1.4.2%20%20ESC%C3%89PTICOS,%20AGN%C3%93STICOS,%20ATEOS.pdf |title=Escepticismo, agnosticismo y ateísmo Concepto de Dios, panteísmo, deismo |date=November 2012 |access-date=13 August 2018 |format=PDF |language=es |first=Miquel Àngel |last=Bosch i Fridrin |work=Mabosch}}</ref> an anglophile and a defender of the [[Age of Enlightenment|Enlightenment]] in the [[Voltaire]] tradition.<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.apostadigital.com/revistav3/hemeroteca/oneca3.pdf |title=Voltaire o el caos de las ideas claras |last=Oneca Agurruza |first=Iñaki |date=11 October 2004 |access-date=13 August 2018 |issn=1696-7348 |journal=Aposta. Revista de Ciencias Sociales |language=es |format=PDF}}</ref>
In November 2012 he was awarded the prestigious [[Octavio Paz]] Prize of Poetry and Essay.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2012/11/16/actualidad/1353093382_007641.html |title=Fernando Savater, premio de Poesía y Ensayo Octavio Paz |last=Constenla |first=Tereixa |date=16 November 2012 |access-date=17 November 2012 |location=Madrid |language=es |newspaper=[[El País]] |publisher=Prisa}}</ref>
He recently founded a new political party called ''Unión, progreso y democracia'' ([[Union, Progress and Democracy]]) with former socialists MP [[Rosa Díez]], [[Albert Boadella]] and [[Mario Vargas Llosa]] in order to oppose different nationalist movements in Spanish mainstream politics.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.elespanol.com/espana/20160918/156484861_0.html |title=Fernando Savater: "Soy de UPyD, pero Ciudadanos es la mejor opción de las que se presentan" |date=19 September 2016 |access-date=13 August 2018 |last=Ramírez |first=Daniel |language=es |newspaper=El Español}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://elpais.com/politica/2016/06/14/actualidad/1465922642_677899.html |title=UPyD se pone las gafas de Savater |last=Mateo |first=Juan José |date=15 June 2016 |access-date=13 August 2018 |location=Madrid |language=es |newspaper=[[El País]] |publisher=Prisa}}</ref> Critics have pointed out that their political outlook seems to be dominated by a strong Spanish nationalist ideology itself.
==Bibliography== *''Nihilismo y acción'' (''Nihilism and Action'') (1970) *''Ensayo sobre Cioran'' (''Essay on Cioran'') (1974) *''Panfleto contra el Todo'' (''A Proclamation against Everything'') (1978) *''Criaturas del aire'' (1979); *''Caronte aguarda'' (''Charon Awaits'') (1981) *''La tarea del héroe'' (''The Task of the Hero'') (1981) *''Invitación a la ética'' (''An Invitation to Ethics'') (1982) *''La infancia recuperada'' (''Childhood Recovered'') (1983) *''Sobre vivir'' (''On Living -and Surviving'') (1983) *''Las razones del antimilitarismo y otras razones'' (''The Reasons for Antimilitarism and Other Reasons'') (1984) *''El contenido de la felicidad'' (''The Contents of Happiness'') (1986) *''Ética como amor propio'' (''Ethics as Self-Esteem'') (1988) *''Ética para Amador'' (''Ethics for Amador'') (1991) *''Política para Amador'' (''Politics for Amador'') (1992) *''Sin contemplaciones'' (''Straight Talk'') (1993) *''Despierta y lee'' (''Wake Up and Read'') (1998) *''Las preguntas de la vida'' (''The Questions of Life'') (1999) *''Perdonen las molestias'' (''Sorry for Disturbing'') (2001) *''El Gran Laberinto'' (''The Great Labyrinth'') (2005) *''Ética de Urgencia'' (''Importunate Ethics'') (2012)
