{{short description|Australian philosopher}} {{Infobox philosopher |region = [[Western philosophy]] |era = [[Contemporary philosophy|21st-century philosophy]] |color = |image = |name = '''Garrett Cullity''' |birth_date = |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |school_tradition = [[Analytic philosophy|Analytic]] | institutions = [[University of Adelaide]] |main_interests = [[moral philosophy]] | thesis_title = | thesis_url = | thesis_year = | doctoral_advisor = | doctoral_students = |notable_ideas = | spouse = | education = [[Oxford University]] (PhD), [[University of Western Australia]] (BA) | alma_mater = |influences = |influenced = |awards = [[Eureka Prize]] |website = http://www.garrettcullity.com/ }}
'''Garrett Michael Cullity''' is an Australian philosopher and Hughes Professor of [[Philosophy]] at the [[University of Adelaide]]. He is known for his research on [[moral philosophy]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Singer |first1=Peter |title=Review Essay on "The Moral Demands of Affluence" |journal=[[Philosophy and Phenomenological Research]] |date=2007 |volume=75 |issue=2 |pages=475–483 |jstor=40041119 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Sonderholm |first1=Jorn |title=The Moral Demands of Affluence: a Logical Problem for Cullity |journal=[[Acta Analytica]] |date=9 February 2015 |volume=30 |issue=4 |pages=409–417 |doi=10.1007/s12136-015-0251-2 |language=en |issn=0353-5150}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Driver |first1=Julia |title=The Moral Demands of Affluence |journal=[[Philosophical Books]] |date=January 2007 |volume=48 |issue=1 |pages=66–70 |doi=10.1111/j.1468-0149.2007.00431.x |language=en |issn=0031-8051}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Brand-Ballard |first1=Jeffrey |title=Review of The Moral Demands of Affluence |journal=Notre Dame Philosophical Reviews |date=13 June 2005 |url=https://ndpr.nd.edu/news/the-moral-demands-of-affluence/ |accessdate=24 October 2018 |issn=1538-1617}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Schmidt |first1=Lucinda |title=Profile: Garrett Cullity |url=https://www.smh.com.au/money/investing/profile-garrett-cullity-20100727-10tv0.html |website=The Sydney Morning Herald |accessdate=24 October 2018 |language=en |date=27 July 2010}}</ref> Cullity is a Fellow of [[Australian Academy of the Social Sciences]] and [[Australian Academy of the Humanities]], and a former president of [[Australasian Association of Philosophy]] (2012-2013).<ref>{{cite web |title=Cullity's CV |url=http://www.garrettcullity.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Cv-May-18.doc |accessdate=31 October 2018}}</ref>
