'''Pedro Cerezo Galán''' (born 14 February 1935, [[Hinojosa del Duque]]) is a Spanish philosopher and university professor. His specialty is contemporary [[Western philosophy]], including modern Spanish thinkers such as [[José Ortega y Gasset]], [[Xavier Zubiri]] and [[Antonio Machado]].

== Biography ==
He graduated from the [[Universidad Complutense de Madrid]] in 1958, with a degree in philosophy and literature, and obtained his doctorate there three years later. His thesis on the concept of [[ousia]] in [[Aristotle]] was published as a book in 1962. This was followed by studies at the [[University of Freiburg]] and the [[University of Heidelberg]]. He was also a [[research fellow|Fellow]] at the [[Spanish National Research Council]], the [[Goethe-Institut]] and the [[Alexander von Humboldt Foundation]].<ref name="R">[https://cordobapedia.wikanda.es/wiki/Pedro_Cerezo_Gal%c3%a1n Brief biography] @ Córdobapedia.</ref>

In 1968, he became an associate professor of philosophy at the [[University of  Barcelona]] then, two years later, obtained the chair of history and philosophy at the  [[University of Granada]], where he remained until his retirement, serving as dean of the Faculty of Philosophy and letters. He is currently a Professor Emeritus.<ref name="R" /> 

In the [[Spanish general election, 1982|general elections of 1982]], he was chosen as a deputy, representing the [[Granada (Spanish Congress electoral district)|District of Granada]] for the [[Spanish Socialist Workers' Party]].<ref>[http://www.congreso.es/portal/page/portal/Congreso/Congreso/Diputados/BusqForm?_piref73_1333155_73_1333154_1333154.next_page=/wc/fichaDiputado?idDiputado=307&idLegislatura=2 Listing] @ the Congreso de los Diputados website.</ref> From 1989 to 1991, he was a member of the advisory committee at the [[Juan March Foundation]]. In 2014, he was awarded the [[Menéndez Pelayo International Prize]].<ref>[http://www.europapress.es/cantabria/noticia-filosofo-pedro-cerezo-galan-premio-internacional-menendez-pelayo-20140723180353.html "El filósofo Pedro Cerezo Galán, Premio Internacional Menéndez Pelayo"] @ EuroPress Cantabria.</ref>

== Selected writings ==
* ''Palabra en el tiempo: Poesía y filosofía en Antonio Machado'', Gredos, 1975 {{ISBN|84-249-0661-6}}
* ''La voluntad de aventura: Aproximaciones críticas al pensamiento de Ortega y Gasset'', Ariel, 1984 {{ISBN|978-84-344-8709-3}}
* ''Las máscaras de lo trágico: Filosofía y tragedia en Miguel de Unamuno'', Trotta, 1996 {{ISBN|978-84-8164-067-0}}
