{{Sangam literature}}
'''Velliveethiyār''' ([[Tamil language|Tamil]]: வெள்ளிவீதியார்) was a poetess of the [[Sangam period]], to whom 14 verses of the Sangam literature have been attributed, including verse 23 of the [[Tiruvalluva Maalai]].<ref name="Vedanayagam_Urai">{{cite book | last = Vedanayagam | first = Rama | author-link = | title = திருவள்ளுவ மாலை மூலமும் எளிய உரை விளக்கமும் [Tiruvalluva Maalai: Moolamum Eliya Urai Vilakkamum] | publisher = Manimekalai Prasuram | series = | volume = | edition = 1 | date = 2017 | location = Chennai | pages = 36–37 | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>
==Biography== Velliveedhiyar lived in the Velliambala Veedhi area of [[Madurai]] and came to be known thus.<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_3">{{cite book | last = Kowmareeshwari (Ed.) | first = S. | author-link = | title = அகநானூறு, புறநானூறு [Agananuru, Purananuru] | publisher = Saradha Pathippagam | series = Sanga Ilakkiyam | volume = 3 | edition = 1 | date = August 2012 | location = Chennai | pages = 251 | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref> She remained separated from her husband, who left her, and spent her remaining life in search of him. Many of her verses reflected her poignant lived experience.<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_2">{{cite book | last = Kowmareeshwari (Ed.) | first = S. | author-link = | title = குறுந்தொகை, பரிபாடல், கலித்தொகை [Kurunthogai, Paripadal, Kalitthogai] | publisher = Saradha Pathippagam | series = Sanga Ilakkiyam | volume = 2 | edition = 1 | date = August 2012 | location = Chennai | pages = 453 | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref> The verses are rife with feministic psychological thoughts.<ref name="Vedanayagam_Urai"/> She has been cited by [[Avvaiyar I]].<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_3"/>
==Contribution to the Sangam literature== Velliveedhiyar has written 14 Sangam verses, including 8 in [[Kurunthogai]] (verses 27, 44, 58, 130, 146, 149, 169, and 386), 3 in [[Natrinai]] (verses 70, 335, and 348), 2 in [[Agananuru]] (verses 45 and 362), and 1 in [[Tiruvalluva Maalai]] (verse 23).<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_2"/>
